  "summary": "Telegram-based exfiltration channel in index.js",
  "details": "static indicator a static pattern match flags index.js lines 86 and 89 invoking api.telegram.org/bot.../sendMessage with chat_id parameters. Telegram Bot API is a well-documented exfiltration channel used by npm supply-chain malware to stage collected data to an attacker-controlled chat. For a package named '0e' (no legitimate product context, minimal files, no the analysis contextual counter-evidence), hardcoded Telegram bot messaging at the main entry is consistent with data relay to attacker infra rather than a legitimate feature. No documented user-facing Telegram integration justifies this in a generically-named utility package.",
